data:
The N stage is determined by the number of lymph nodes with cancer.
N0 indicates no lymph node involvement.
N1 indicates metastasis in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes.
N2 indicates metastasis in 4 to 9 axillary lymph nodes.
N3 indicates metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes.

The N stage is determined by the number of lymph nodes with cancer.

N1 indicates metastasis in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes.
N2 indicates metastasis in 4 to 9 axillary lymph nodes.
N3 indicates metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes.
The N stage is assigned based on the number of positive lymph nodes and the total number of sampled lymph nodes.
